Functtion to get time series and STL decomposition based on each sector

In [34]:
def my_decom(given_df, given_sec):
    res_list = []
    ready_list=[]
    
    ### Getting all the sereis ready for decomposition in list
    for i in range(0, len(given_sec)):
        df = given_df.loc[given_df.sector == given_sec[i]]
        sec_close_series = df.sec_rel_close.copy()
        sec_close_series.index = df.date_dt.copy()
        sec_ready_series = sec_close_series.copy().resample('W').last()
        res_list.append(sec_ready_series)
     
    ### Using the ready sereis to create a STL decomposition for all sectors.
    for i in range(0, len(given_sec)):
        ready_list.append( STL(res_list[i]).fit() )
        
        
    return ready_list

Function that creates a dataframe, extracts rel_close_price into series, makes the series ready for time series, resamples the series (weekly) and appends the final results to a list for each company

In [49]:
def my_each_comp_decom(given_df, given_comp):
    res_list = []
    ready_list=[]
    
    ### Getting all the sereis ready for decomposition in list
    for i in range(0, len(given_comp)):
        df = given_df.loc[given_df.symbol == given_comp[i]]
        company_close_series = df.company_rel_close.copy()
        company_close_series.index = df.date_dt.copy()
        company_ready_series = company_close_series.copy().resample('W').last()
        res_list.append(company_ready_series)
     
    ### Using the ready sereis to create a STL decomposition for all companies.
    for i in range(0, len(given_comp)):
        ready_list.append( STL(res_list[i]).fit() )
        
        
    return ready_list

Function to create a dataframe for seasonal and trend component values of each company

In [51]:
def get_trend_seasonal_val(decom_res, given_comp):
    ready_df = pd.DataFrame()
    
    for i in range(0, len(given_comp)):
        # getting seasonal values
        seasonal_val = decom_res[i].seasonal
        
        # getting trend values
        trend_val = decom_res[i].trend
        
        # merging seasonal and trend value for each company
        temp_df = pd.concat([seasonal_val, trend_val], axis=1).reset_index()
        
        # adding the compnay name to the dataframe
        temp_df['symbol'] = given_comp[i]
        
        # merging all companies in one dataframe
        ready_df = pd.concat([ready_df, temp_df])
        
    return ready_df

Creating Monthly Dataframe¶

Creating the same dataframe as above but instead on weekly time series we will resample monthly just for the sake of less computing while modelling with the seasonal and trend values

Same decoomposition function as above just the resampling value is changed.

In [70]:
def my_each_comp_decom_month_end(given_df, given_comp):
    res_list = []
    ready_list=[]
    
    ### Getting all the sereis ready for decomposition in list
    for i in range(0, len(given_comp)):
        df = given_df.loc[given_df.symbol == given_comp[i]]
        company_close_series = df.company_rel_close.copy()
        company_close_series.index = df.date_dt.copy()
        ### changing the resampling value to month end M
        company_ready_series = company_close_series.copy().resample('M').last()
        res_list.append(company_ready_series)
     
    ### Using the ready sereis to create a STL decomposition for all companies.
    for i in range(0, len(given_comp)):
        ready_list.append( STL(res_list[i]).fit() )
        
        
    return ready_list
